Description: Fragment of oval handle, rising to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine orange-pink; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Aristopolis. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 101a, 57. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 033.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1156)
